{{Undisclosed paid|date=September 2017}} {{Infobox book | name = A House in the Sky | title_orig = | translator = | image = A House in the Sky.jpg | caption = | author = [[Amanda Lindhout]] and Sara Corbett | illustrator = | cover_artist = | country = | language = English | series = | genre = Memoir | publisher = | release_date = 2013 | english_release_date = | media_type = Print | pages = | isbn = 978-1451645613 }}
'''''A House in the Sky''''' is a 2013 memoir by [[Amanda Lindhout]], co-written with the journalist Sara Corbett. It recounts Lindhout's experience in southern [[Somalia]] as a hostage of teenage militants from the [[Hizbul Islam]] fundamentalist group. As of September 2013, the book is a ''[[New York Times]]'' bestseller.<ref name="Best Sellers -September 29, 2013">{{cite news |url=https://www.nytimes.com/best-sellers-books/2013-09-29/e-book-nonfiction/list.html |title=Best Sellers -September 29, 2013 |date=2013-09-29 |publisher=''[[New York Times]]'' |first=Gregory |last=Cowles}}</ref> It also won the 2014 [[Canadian Broadcasting Corporation|CBC]] Bookie Award for Best Canadian Nonfiction<ref>{{cite news |url=http://www.cbc.ca/books/the-bookies-2014-vote-for-the-best-books-of-the-past-year.html |title=The Bookies 2014: The Winners |accessdate=February 10, 2014 |publisher=[[Canadian Broadcasting Corporation|CBC]]}}</ref> and was nominated for the 2014 Libris Award for best non-fiction book of 2013.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.newswire.ca/en/story/1340349/libris-awards-2014-shortlist-revealed |title=Libris Awards 2014 Shortlist Revealed |date=April 16, 2014 |accessdate=May 8, 2014}}</ref> The book was optioned in 2014 by [[Megan Ellison]] in order to create a screen adaptation of the work. [[Rooney Mara]] will play Lindhout in the film version.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.thewrap.com/rooney-mara-to-star-in-a-house-in-the-sky-for-megan-ellisons-annapurna/ |title=Rooney Mara to Star in 'A House in the Sky' for Megan Ellison's Annapurna |author=Jordan Zakarin |date=June 25, 2014 |accessdate=June 25, 2014 |publisher=''The Wrap''}}</ref>
