'''WikiArt'''<ref>[http://theteachingpalette.com/2011/11/20/wikipaintings-a-fantastic-new-artist-resource/ WikiPaintings: A Fantastic New Artist Resource]</ref><ref>[http://www.oprah.com/blogs/At-Last-Internet-That-Makes-Your-Brain-Better At Last: The World&#39;s Best Paintings, On Your Computer Screen] (Oprah Winfrey ''Life Lift'')</ref> (formerly known as '''WikiPaintings''') is an online, user-editable visual art [[encyclopedia]]. Based upon a statement in its 2013 financial report,<ref>http://blog.wikipaintings.org/2014/01/financial-report-2013.html</ref> the site appears to have been online since 2010. They claim to have reached 75,000 paintings as of June 2012.<ref>WikiPaintings blog entry: [http://blog.wikipaintings.org/2012/06/75000-paintings.html ''We've reached the point of 75000 paintings'']</ref>.
{{As of|2017|7}}, the site shows the following numbers: * 2672 artists ([https://www.wikiart.org/en/artists-by-art-movement 156 movements] in 2-level hierarchy, [https://www.wikiart.org/en/artists-by-painting-school 253 schools/groups], [https://www.wikiart.org/en/artists-by-genre 50 genres], [https://www.wikiart.org/en/artists-by-field 28 fields], [https://www.wikiart.org/en/artists-by-nation 87 nationalities]) * 146509 artworks ([https://www.wikiart.org/en/paintings-by-style 160 styles], [https://www.wikiart.org/en/paintings-by-genre 54 genres]) * Taking for example [https://www.wikiart.org/en/salvador-dali/ Salvador Dali], we see 1102 artworks, his creative Periods, and related artists.
{{As of|2013|2}} "the Wiki functionality of the site is still under development".<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.wikipaintings.org/en/About|title=About|publisher=WikiPaintings|accessdate=22 February 2013}}</ref> The developers are based in Ukraine.<ref>WikiPaintings blog: [http://blog.wikipaintings.org/ Financial Report 2012 Q1] ("...our country (Ukraine) doesn’t support...")</ref>
